Would it be feasible to have a browser command that refreshes a page without images, even if the images had already been loaded? 
Could this be done without clearing the whole cache? 
In other words, I'd like to be able to toggle images on and off, if for example, I want to access alt text. 
Does this sound like a useful feature? 
